Nissan to Recall Pathfinders, QX4 SUV on Rust, Detroit News Says

-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 
2011-04-25T09:09:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/nissan-to-recall-pathfinders-qx4-suv-on-rust-detroit-news-says.html
Nissan Motor Co. plans to recall at
least 195,000 Pathfinder and Infiniti QX4 SUVs because of
concern rust might cause the steering column to break, the
 Detroit News  reported, citing a notice posted on a government
website.  The recall will affect 162,658, 1996-2004 Pathfinder and
33,333, 1997-2003 Infiniti QX4 vehicles sold or registered in 20
states that use heavy amounts of road salt in cold weather, the
newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Kraus at 
 jkraus2@bloomberg.net  